I expanded your example to show it only works with 0 or 1.


    import re
    
    a = &quot;00001&quot;
    b = &quot;00011&quot; 
    c = &quot;00111&quot;  
    d = &quot;01001&quot;
    e = &quot;10001&quot;
    f = &quot;52255&quot;
    g = &quot;90099&quot;
    h = &quot;81811&quot;
    
    def parse(s):
        &quot;&quot;&quot;Parse binary string into like groups.&quot;&quot;&quot;
